<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1764" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1764">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/207.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Cresson</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram October 15. Minister Price before leaving conveyed
                            to Panaman President sense of above. He regrets that Santos Railway
                            could not be included but expressed willingness to meet Department’s
                            position. No further developments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cresson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>